  "statement": "Let $a, b \\in \\mathbb{R}$ with $a < b$. Suppose that $f : [a,b] \\to \\mathbb{R}$ is continuous on $[a,b]$, differentiable on $(a,b)$, and satisfies $f(a) = f(b)$. Then there exists $c \\in (a,b)$ such that\n\\[\nf'(c) = 0.\n\\]",
